e9d4aa03-c927-492c-a1dc-34b8e6c3f032.title: <player>
e9d4aa03-c927-492c-a1dc-34b8e6c3f032.text: What's with the glowing portal thing?

8208165a-17e1-4a27-8ac7-bbef907f3c54.title: <player>
8208165a-17e1-4a27-8ac7-bbef907f3c54.text: Who are you and what are you doing?

713f92d0-4dd3-428c-9ea0-77976d84a34a.title: Squire
713f92d0-4dd3-428c-9ea0-77976d84a34a.text:
It's because of something the Temple Knights have,
called the Gaze of Saradomin. They get the option of
being brought to Falador when they die, so Death has
to maintain a presence in the area.

4ef96a4e-2627-42f8-9c2a-74e65737b5c6.title: Squire
4ef96a4e-2627-42f8-9c2a-74e65737b5c6.text:
That portal takes you to Death's own realm. He's got
portals in all the places where people go when they die -
Lumbridge, Edgeville and the rest. I hate it - the thing's
terrifying!

options.text: Who are you and what are you doing?
Tell me about this place.
I'll leave you alone.

eecafc61-605b-4fe5-bc5d-d060b714863c.title: Squire
eecafc61-605b-4fe5-bc5d-d060b714863c.text:
This place? It's the castle crypt. The greatest White
Knights are buried here, after a lifetime in the service
of Saradomin. At least, that's how it used to be.

a0c13b4d-0eaa-48f8-87cf-c6497a4316fd.title: Squire
a0c13b4d-0eaa-48f8-87cf-c6497a4316fd.text:
When I was a new recruit, they brought me here and
told me that if I served Saradomin faithfully, and with
distinction, maybe I'd earn the honour of burial in this
place too.

a0db9f79-cbb0-4557-ab08-eaf4c4d2b33f.title: Squire
a0db9f79-cbb0-4557-ab08-eaf4c4d2b33f.text:
But if you think about it, that's never going to happen -
there just isn't space for more tombs! Anyway, my plan
is to avoid dying, and maybe marry one of the
barmaids when I retire.

options.text: Who are you and what are you doing?
What's with the glowing portal thing?
I'll leave you alone.

4c0c034a-3987-4ff7-933b-b6a66bfefe63.title: Squire
4c0c034a-3987-4ff7-933b-b6a66bfefe63.text:
I'm Vicks, squire to Sir Culler Flife. He's away on a
surveillance mission to Burthorpe, so he sent me down
here to do some cleaning.

options.text: You don't seem to be cleaning much.
What's your master doing in Burthorpe?
Tell me about this place.
What's with the glowing portal thing?
I'll leave you alone.

f23d5fe8-15fa-4ea2-92a2-684a913f2992.title: <player>
f23d5fe8-15fa-4ea2-92a2-684a913f2992.text: You don't seem to be cleaning much.

7bd08c92-3444-41fe-8c91-9e0ba8397d95.title: <player>
7bd08c92-3444-41fe-8c91-9e0ba8397d95.text: What's your master doing in Burthorpe?

74ad0fb8-16a2-4f67-8647-152e0156e545.title: Squire
74ad0fb8-16a2-4f67-8647-152e0156e545.text:
Keeping an eye on those Imperial Guard. We can't
trust 'em, you know. But I shouldn't talk about his
mission.

options.text: Tell me about this place.
What's with the glowing portal thing?
I'll leave you alone.

50462861-88eb-477d-966d-792184002243.title: Squire
50462861-88eb-477d-966d-792184002243.text:
Don't tell the knights, but I'm just not in the mood for
it! I've served for years, and worked really hard, but
they're not even thinking of making me a knight.

2abf1804-49db-4e70-9e5d-3d5feff5b389.title: Squire
2abf1804-49db-4e70-9e5d-3d5feff5b389.text:
I don't know what the problem is. At my last review, I
heard the examiner muttering something about my
name, but I've no idea what he meant by that.
